This paper deals with type systems and concurrency, which are both topics that fall under the programming languages (cs.PL) and operating systems (cs.OS) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses deadlock prevention, which is a common problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper also touches on lock ordering, which is a topic related to concurrency and synchronization (cs.LO).
